re criminalised through detention processes, while being deprived of the right to be heard. This book promotes child-friendly practices in the international migration context, with a view to safeguarding the fundamental rights of unaccompanied minors experiencing detention upon arrival in host countries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aJuvenile detentionzGreece. 0aNoncitizen detention centerszGreece. 0aUnaccompanied immigrant childrenxGovernment policyzGreece. 0aUnaccompanied immigrant childrenzGreece. 0aUnaccompanied refugee childrenxGovernment policyzGreece. 0aUnaccompanied refugee childrenxLegal status, laws, etczGreece. 0aUnaccompanied refugee childrenxLegal status, laws, etc.zGreece. 0aUnaccompanied refugee childrenxServices forzGreece. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831111967940 cprintz978152922286940uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529222883?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529222883423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529222883/original  a978-3-11-119679-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles